			<p>Hey Ree, just so you know, the sublime refers to the concept of the sublime was refined by a British philosopher/poet in the 19th century named Edmund Burke. Technically speaking, the sublime is something so terrible (in a good way?), so wonder-ful and so awe-inspiring that it makes the individual confront his or her own mortality; it is something that puts the fear of God into you. I&#8217;m a 22 year old English major, thank cilantro I finally found some use for my overpriced education. </p>
<p>Also, I can&#8217;t wait to make this!</p>
<p><em>Oooh, thank you Charlotte! I assumed it meant &#8220;perfect,&#8221; and your definition is much better.<br />
Yer reeeeeeal smaert. <img src='http://static.thepioneerwoman.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif' alt=';)' class='wp-smiley' /><br />
