			<h4>Deanna B <span>On Sunday, March 9 at 9:29 pm</span></h4>
			<p>Looks delicious!</p>
<p>As to the sesame allergy, you could try using an unsweetened nut butter (peanut, almond, etc) unless they are allergic to them all. It will make the dressing thicker, and more like a Thai peanut sauce but it would still be tasty. </p>
<p>Oh, and I totally bust out the microplane for ginger. It grates it all nice and fine, and I don&#8217;t have to peel it because the peel doesn&#8217;t go through. (its also easier to grate when frozen)</p>
