		<p class="comment-number">83</p>
		<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/10b2e7449e1cb838456805d6512fde98?s=42&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fthepioneerwoman.com%2Fcooking%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2Fmulti%2Fimages%2Fcomment-avatar-3.gif%3Fs%3D42&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-42 photo' height='42' width='42' />		<div class="comment-text">
			<h4>hana <span>On Sunday, March 9 at 9:53 pm</span></h4>
			<p>Mmmm&#8230;. yes, you can make quite a few substitutions with this salad. If you add different ingredients that aren&#8217;t that asian, just do what the dining establishments here in the City of Angels do and call it a &#8220;fusion&#8221; salad. </p>
<p>And yes, seconding Deanna&#8217;s tip on using the microplane (or a gratting device), but only after you&#8217;ve frozen the ginger. Keeps the ginger fresh and makes it easier to manuver when grating.</p>
