	<div class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-10630">
		<span class="comment-bubble"></span>
		<p class="comment-number">88</p>
		<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/195f2ab6caf55c7897f4047a7bc0c5fa?s=42&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fthepioneerwoman.com%2Fcooking%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2Fmulti%2Fimages%2Fcomment-avatar-3.gif%3Fs%3D42&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-42 photo' height='42' width='42' />		<div class="comment-text">
			<h4><a href='http://OgBlog.net' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Earl</a> <span>On Sunday, March 9 at 10:09 pm</span></h4>
			<p>We ALWAYS order something very similar to this in Santa Rosa, California &#8211; at Pho Vietnam, where the &#8220;salad&#8221; is piled on top of a bowl of vermicelli (rice noodles) and then you get your choice of grilled chicken, or steak, or spring rolls, or whatever, placed on top.  THEN you get to pour on the sauce, which is not so chunky as this one, but quite as good&#8230;..</p>
<p>The only difference I can think of is that their salad has both cilantro AND mint leaves&#8230;&#8230;plus a little bit of asian fish sauce.  </p>
<p>I&#8217;ll be making this salad for sure, and if it&#8217;s as good as Pho Vietnam&#8217;s, it truly will be heavenly!</p>
